These experiences have been shown to build children's confidence and pleasure in physical activities 

187
00:14:37,530 --> 00:14:42,130
Develop their motor skills , and even improve emotional wellbeing 

188
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:49,190
To begin with , children seem to have a natural desire to overcome challenges and take risks 

189
00:14:49,330 --> 00:14:52,570
Taking healthy risks through physical movement

190
00:14:52,570 --> 00:14:58,910
Builds children's confidence and ability to solve problems and persist through frustration 

191
00:14:59,630 --> 00:15:05,020
Secondly , movement activities build children's big body skills

192
00:15:05,020 --> 00:15:07,610
Such as coordination and balance 

193
00:15:07,770 --> 00:15:12,550
As well as the fine motor skills they need for tasks like writing 

194
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:16,070
Tying their shoes or throwing and catching a ball 

195
00:15:16,530 --> 00:15:20,750
Thirdly , according to the american psychological association 

196
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:25,000
Regular physical activity and especially outdoor activity 

197
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,560
Reduces children's stress and depression

198
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:30,760
And improve their ability to focus and learn 

199
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:35,890
Regular exercise can significantly improve self regulation

200
00:15:35,890 --> 00:15:40,820
And decrease disciplinary consequences for negative behaviour 

201
00:15:40,820 --> 00:15:45,190
Physical activity provides a positive outlet for frustration 

202
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:47,110
Anxiety or anger

203
00:15:47,110 --> 00:15:50,910
And can become a healthy coping skill throughout life 

204
00:15:51,510 --> 00:15:57,270
